    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_507172">The email was about some of my account info being changed and I haven't played SCII in months now. Everything about this email looked legit, no spelling/grammar errors and all the urls looked legit, hell they are legit other than the one about changing your info or whatever. The only difference I can spot is that in the &quot;From&quot; field it says noreply @ blizzard. com, which is a legit email that Blizzard uses, but in one other email I have thats really from them it says its from Blizzard Entertainment. <br />
<br />
Well, thanks FireFox for stopping that one. <br />
<br />
I guess this is some scam that is primarily used against WoW players and accounts?</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
