    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_507218">I've had links that were legit get flagged by thunderbird, heck my Blizzcon pet code email had thunderbird screaming at me that this was insecure and probably malicious as the link was masquerading as something else. I didn't go through with following the link seeing that obviously. The easier solution is always to ignore any links in anything sent to you asking for your info, run noscript, block crap from running, and go in manually to battlenet like you would normally do and check there (that's what I did with the code, worked fine typed in to the box there so someone at rayv just ****ed up big time when they were sending out the codes). So it could be legit, some Blizzard emails look funky even though they are legit... but I still wouldn't follow any link or allow it to show anything that can run scripts.</div>
