    <div align="left" id="post_message_507300">How hard is it, don't give your username and and password to anyone! <br />
<br />
If you think you won something either it's in your mailbox IN GAME, or you didn't really win anything!<br />
<br />
If blizzard needs to get a hold of you they will talk to you in game. The only thing I could imagine they would send you a real email on would be if your credit card couldn't charge for whatever reason and i doubt that would have any links in it. <br />
<br />
Which brings me to if you get an email that you think may be real, don't risk it. What it takes the slowest typist in the world 30 seconds to type in blizzards address? Quit being lazy type it in yourself and save the link!<br />
<br />
<u>Why I don't have an authenticator (may be incorrect info)</u><br />
Ok, my understanding on the Authenticator is that you have to put in your password along with the auth key every single time! I know I said don't be lazy earlier but why keep your password if you are going to force me to put in a random key?</div>
