    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_507309">Actually, it's a token generator. It generates a new 6-digit code every few minutes (maybe every minute, not sure). <br />
You need to enter the 6-digit code in addition to your password. Only if both are correct, you can log in.<br />
<br />
The 6-digit codes generated are unique to that authenticator, so you can only log in with exactly THE authenticator that has been connected to your account.<br />
<br />
If a hacker manages to get hold of your account name and password, he still can't log in unless he physically holds your authenticator OR gets the generated code during the time it's valid (about a minute). <br />
<br />
BTW - this applies to both the .battle-Net-Account page as well as logging into a game.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
