    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_507316">I had the keychain version for a while, but have had it on my phone since I got a smart phone earlier this year.  I started using it when my GL got hacked, figured a keylogger came with a addon.  For 5$ and now free if you have a smart phone it is completely worth the time it can save you.  <br />
<br />
Think about how long you'll have to be on the phone with Blizzard, and time your account will be frozen while they investigate.. then how long till you get your items back. vs. free phone app or 5$.<br />
<br />
The keychain generates a 6 digit code.<br />
My phone app generates a 8 digit code.<br />
Afiak there is no current way to fake them, but if someone got a bit of maleware on your system that keylogged and blocked the code from being sent. They could get access to your account once.<br />
<br />
Biggwin, people don't give out their user/pass most of the time.  It's emails like this, or buying gold, even maleware in addons that get most. Thanks to places like curse addons have gotten safer.</div>
