	<div align="left"><b><div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>Biggwin said:</strong></div></b></div></td>
 
	</tr>
  <tr>   
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/openq.gif" width="30" height="30" ></td>
    <td>
		<div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">How hard is it, don't give your username and and password to anyone! </div>
		</td>
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/closeq.gif" width="30" height="30" align="right"></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</div>My wife's account was never given to anyone.  Even I didn't know the account info - I could have I just never needed it.  She didn't use add-ons, she was pretty much the definition of a casual player.  Also, wow and Steam games were about the only things she did on that machine - web browsing is almost 100% exclusive to the laptop - and that was the only machine she ever logged into WoW from.<br />
<br />
She got hacked.  Twice in a row.  Bought an Authenticator, recovered the account for a third time, hasn't been hacked since.</div>
