Yeap.  In fact, it happened shortly after she converted her account to battle.net, which is what made the e-mail account the userid.  I will say the one mistake she made was having a password that was a dictionary word plus a number (a 1 at the end), which made it much easier to brute force.  Had I known her account info I can assure you that particular mistake would never have happened.  It's a nice random string now. <img src="images/smilies/emote_smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smile" class="inlineimg" /></div>
