    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_507416">just an FYI to those that use gmail..<br />
<br />
if your gmail address is <a href="mailto:yourname@gmail.com">yourname@gmail.com</a> you can sign up for things like battlenet with <a href="mailto:your.name@gmail.com">your.name@gmail.com</a> and still receive all emails.<br />
<br />
google ignores any period before the @ symbol.<br />
<br />
so the following all work:<br />
<br />
<a href="mailto:y.ourname@gmail.com">y.ourname@gmail.com</a><br />
<a href="mailto:yo.urname@gmail.com">yo.urname@gmail.com</a><br />
<a href="mailto:yournam.e@gmail.com">yournam.e@gmail.com</a><br />
<a href="mailto:you.rna.me@gmail.com">you.rna.me@gmail.com</a><br />
<br />
They all show up in your inbox and you can setup filters to  apply labels to specific ones for easier identification.<br />
<br />
just something to keep in mind when signing up for various sites/services on the net.<br />
<br />
and Authenticator in any form is your best friend.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
