    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_507469">Additionally, anything after a + sign is ignored by gmail as well.<br />
<br />
I typically sign up for new webservices with myname+nameofservice@gmail.com<br />
<br />
For example, I just made an account at Barnes and Noble, so I signed up with pyrocat+bn@gmail.com. Low and behold I started getting spam addressed to pyrocat+bn@gmail.com so I simply went into gmail filters and said to automatically mark everything sent to pyrocat+bn@gmail.com as spam. If I'm expecting an e-mail from them (like order confirmation) I can unblock it temporarily or look in my spam folder <img src="images/smilies/emote_smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smile" class="inlineimg" /></div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
<br>
<table width="100%%"  border="0" cellpadding="3">
<tr>
<td>


</td>
 </tr>
</table>
 

</div>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

